description: Dit is het data bestand voor tv_grab_nl_py en wordt bij elke run gedownload
Raise the version for any source to force downloading the corresponding file afresh.
Keep this number the same in the source file!
Raise if needed the data_version to send the users the warning_message with
the corresponing number, with the warning to run --configure to implement it.
This last is not needed for updates not needing --configure. (that do not influence

10: New NPO and VPRO sources and DPG media ID changes, please rerun --configure.
9: New DPG media sources, please rerun --configure.
8: Horizon.tv's station ids have changed, please rerun --configure.
7: Horizon.tv's station ids have changed, please rerun --configure.
6:
The npo.nl source has been reactivated, but as the channelids
have all changed you need to run --configure to use it.
It now gives basic listings for all the NPO channels for up to 2 weeks.
Unfortunatly only start time and titel and no longer for the regional channels.
5:
While we are working on a renewed source-file for the new npo.nl site
this source is disabled! Further news follows in the comming days.
4: Wild FM changed name to Wild Hitradio.
2:
HBO and Fox Life have closed.
Omroep Brabant is now 24/7 on Canal Digitaal, use 0-114.
1:
Nickelodeon and Spike changes, use the following:
         0-89: Nickelodeon 24/7.
        0-467: Spike 24/7.
1-nickelodeon: Combined Nickelodeon/Spike.

--description--: If no extension is provided .png will be assumed
This is a dict of channel combinations. If the combination exists on one of the sources,
that source suplies the chanid, else a virtual chanid is created
every definition is a list of channels to be merged into this chanid
It at least contains a chanid, but can also be a dict with next to the chanid a start and end time
If in a definition any times are provided the following rules apply!
For these times the above 'combined-channels-tz' timezone must be used!
If start or end time is invalid, it is removed. Next missing start/end times will get replaced by 0:00/24:00
If the children do overlap, end times will get truncated! So if they align you can leave out end times,
but partially leaving out start times will probably result in a cuckoo pushing the other(s) out!
If you want a child to fill-up certain slots, you can add a slots keyword followed by a list of names
This should be a dict with the new chanid as key (in stead of --example--)
inside you have the old chanid from which is merging into the new one, a set of sourceid/channel combinations
the date of implementation (yyyymmdd) and a message to the users as in the example below
